Nashitomi no Mikoto is enshrined as a deity at the *{{ill|Omi Shrine (Yogo)|lt=Noimi Shrine|ja|乃彌神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omi Shrine (Yogo)|qq=}}*, a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} in Ōmi Province, where he is worshipped alongside his brother Omishiru no Mikoto at the *{{ill|lt=Omi Shrine|Omi Shrine (Yogo)|ja|乎彌神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lt=Omi Shrine|qq=}}*, which incorporated Noimi Shrine. Additionally, he is also enshrined at *{{ill|Ōfura Shrine|ja|意富布良神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōfura Shrine|qq=}}* as a subordinate deity.
== Genealogy == Nashitomi no Mikoto was the son of {{ill|Igatsuomi no Mikoto|ja|伊賀津臣命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Igatsuomi no Mikoto|qq=}} and father of {{ill|Kamikikikatsu|lt=Kamikikikatsu no Mikoto|ja|神聞勝命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamikikikatsu|qq=}}. His descendants include prominent clans such as the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatomi clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Ōnakatomi clan|ja|大中臣氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōnakatomi clan|qq=}}, and {{ill|Fujiwara clan|ja|藤原氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara clan|qq=}}.
The *{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=}}* identifies him as the ancestor of the Kawamatauji no Muraji of {{ill|Kawachi Province|ja|河内国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawachi Province|qq=}}.
